Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the management of channel congestions, which involves information theory and signal processing, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a likely category as well. Additionally, the paper discusses the reliability of applications, which is related to cybersecurity, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) a possible category. The paper also discusses the applicability and efficiency of congestion control mechanisms, which involves system modeling and optimization, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the adoption of modulation and coding schemes, which is related to computer systems and hardware, making cs.CY (Computers and Society) a possible category.
